                     <h3 style="color:brown">Domestic Baggage allowance</h3>
                    <p style="text-align:justify">
1.Hand Baggage: One hand bag up to 7 kgs and 115 cms (L+W+H), shall be allowed per customer. For contactless travel we recommend to place it under the seat in front, on board.<br>
2.Check In Baggage: NIL<br>
3.Passengers may carry up to 5 Litres of alcoholic beverages as part of their checked-in baggage,<br>provided the following conditions are met:<br>
4.The alcoholic beverage is in retail packaging and is packed appropriately (to prevent damage / leakage).<br>
5.Alcohol content in the beverage is not more than 70%.<br>
6.If the alcoholic beverage contains 24% or less alcohol by volume the above limitation of 5 Litres does not apply.<br>
7.The alcoholic beverages is also permitted in carry-on baggage when purchased from the Airport Security Hold Area and should be placed in a transparent re-sealable plastic bag of a maximum capacity not exceeding 1 Litre. The indicative size of the 1 Litre bag is: 20.5 cm x 20.5 cm or 25 cm x 15 cm or equivalent. The containers must fit comfortably within the bag, which should be fully closed.<br>
8.The passengers must comply with other applicable state / national regulations, if any.</p></center>  
                    
